## 4. Template Use Notes

- Ask the requester for missing values before generation when a `TBD` would affect scope, behavior, actor, business rule, acceptance, evidence, or ownership.
- No `TBD` may remain when status is `Approved` or `Ready for delivery` unless it is listed in Section 11 as an assumption, risk, deferred item, or blocker with an owner and needed-by date.
- Create one package folder per FR at `docs/02-product/FR/fr-<nnn>/`.
- Keep detailed FR content in the package `fr-<nnn>-description.md` from `templates/fr-record-template.md.tmpl`; keep this document as the index, readiness gate, summary, and cross-FR traceability view.
- Merge linked user story context into each package `fr-<nnn>-description.md`: story statement, feature objective, user or business value, primary scenario, story-derived constraints, and relevant story acceptance criteria. Do not leave feature detail only in a backlog/story link.
- Each FR package must contain `fr-<nnn>-description.md`, `fr-<nnn>-test-cases.md`, `sequence.mmd`, `sequence.drawio` when required, and `fr-<nnn>-lld.md` from `templates/fr-lld-template.md.tmpl`.
- Keep each acceptance criterion independently testable in the FR package description file. Every `Must` FR requires at least one happy path, one alternate/edge path, and one permission/error path unless explicitly justified.
- Generate draft test cases in the FR package `fr-<nnn>-test-cases.md` from the acceptance criteria. Final test design, execution, and evidence remain owned by `ai-quality-engineer`.
- Use `sequence.mmd` as the MermaidJS source and `sequence.drawio` as the editable companion in the same FR package folder. For simple single-step FRs, record `Not required - single-step behavior`.
- Mermaid safety: avoid semicolons in sequence message text because some renderers treat `;` as a statement separator. Use ` - ` or `,` instead. Avoid raw pipes, unmatched brackets/quotes, and HTML-like angle brackets in labels. Quote participant labels that contain punctuation or slashes, for example `participant API as ".NET Retention API Job"`.
- Make traceable items and outputs clickable. Link FR IDs to package description files, AC IDs to anchors inside the package description file, test case IDs to anchors inside `fr-<nnn>-test-cases.md`, and sequence/Draw.io/LLD artifacts to the same package folder. If the target path or anchor is not yet known, keep the ID visible and list the missing link in Section 13 as an evidence gap.
- Do not mark an FR `Ready for delivery` or `Approved` if its only story/backlog trace is an `FR-Q-*` blocker, open question, or generic `TBD`. Delivery-ready FRs require actual backlog/story and test/validation links.

