## 8. Acceptance Criteria

Use stable scenario IDs and Given/When/Then format. Each `Must` FR needs at least one happy path, one relevant edge/alternate path, and one error/permission/exception path unless explicitly justified.
Each scenario must be independently testable and should avoid compound `Then` clauses. If a scenario needs multiple evidence checks, split it into separate AC IDs or list sub-checks under one unambiguous outcome.

### FR-001.AC1 - Happy path
Given ...
When ...
Then ...

### FR-001.AC2 - Edge or alternate path
Given ...
When ...
Then ...

### FR-001.AC3 - Error, permission, or exception path
Given ...
When ...
Then ...

